From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: therockbot <therockbot@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] rpp: make public include directories relocatable

TheRock builds rpp with an empty ROCM_PATH (-DROCM_PATH=), matching the
convention used for every other ROCm subproject. rpp's fallback
`set(ROCM_PATH /opt/rocm CACHE PATH ...)` cannot override an already-set
(empty) cache entry, so ROCM_PATH stays empty and the unwrapped
`${ROCM_PATH}/include` public include directory collapses to the absolute
path `/include`.

Because that entry is not wrapped in a BUILD_INTERFACE/INSTALL_INTERFACE
generator expression (unlike the neighboring api entry), it is exported
verbatim into the installed lib/cmake/rpp/rpp-targets.cmake. Any consumer
(e.g. the packaged rpp test suite, which calls find_package(rpp)) then
fails configuration with:

  CMake Error in CMakeLists.txt:
    Imported target "rpp::rpp" includes non-existent path
      "/include"
    in its INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES.

Make the entry relocatable: use ${ROCM_PATH}/include only in the build
tree (BUILD_INTERFACE) and advertise the install-tree include directory
(INSTALL_INTERFACE) to downstream consumers instead of baking an absolute
path. The HIP/ROCm host headers are also supplied transitively via the
PUBLIC hip::host link dependency, so no consumer-visible headers are lost.

Upstream tracking: https://github.com/ROCm/rocm-libraries/pull/8295
Once that merges and TheRock's rocm-libraries submodule is bumped past it,
this patch can be dropped.

Signed-off-by: therockbot <therockbot@amd.com>
---
 projects/rpp/CMakeLists.txt | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/projects/rpp/CMakeLists.txt b/projects/rpp/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/projects/rpp/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/projects/rpp/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -366,7 +366,8 @@ set_target_properties(${PROJECT_NAME} PROPERTIES VERSION ${PROJECT_VERSION} SOVE
 target_include_directories(${PROJECT_NAME}
     PUBLIC
         "$<BUILD_INTERFACE:${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/api>"
-        "${ROCM_PATH}/include"
+        "$<BUILD_INTERFACE:${ROCM_PATH}/include>"
+        "$<INSTALL_INTERFACE:${CMAKE_INSTALL_INCLUDEDIR}>"
     PRIVATE
         "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/src/include/cpu"
         "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/src/include/common"
-- 
